commitResults.messageBody:
AB3 only parses strings in existing commands. This limitation
affects how we handle parsing other data types. Expanding the
parsing capabilities to include numbers and date times will enhance
the functionality and flexibility of the system, allowing for more
comprehensive command processing.
Let's Create two new utility classes to parse numbers and date times
from commands. Integrate custom parsing with exception handling
that aligns with AB3s existing framework. This approach ensures
consistency with AB3s current architecture and error-handling
mechanisms, facilitating seamless integration and maintaining code
quality.

Add parent command for sub commands

AB3 only parses strings in existing commands. This limitation
affects how we handle parsing other data types. Expanding the
parsing capabilities to include numbers and date times will enhance
the functionality and flexibility of the system.
Let's create a new parent command for lessons to hand subcommands.
This multi level allows easier handling of similar multi level
commands.

Create new storage to store lesson schedules

There are only 2 data stored in the model and storage. They are
person and userPrefs. This has to be expanded to store lesson and
schedules.
Let's create a new model and Jsonserializable called lesson
schedule. This approach closely follows the current implementation
for addressbook and userPrefs storage. The StorageManager will now
take these 3 storages.

Add testing for AddLessonCommand, AddLessonCommandParser, DateTime,
EndDateTime, Lesson, LocationIndex, StartDateTime, StudentId,
UniqueLessonList
